The background shows a cozy puppet shop with wooden shelves full of other handcrafted toys, softly blurred to maintain focus on the dragons. Lighting is soft and ambient, casting warm shadows that enhance the rich wooden textures. The entire scene evokes a whimsical but grounded tone, blending craftsmanship with personality.

Style:
Photorealistic, warm indoor lighting, rich woodgrain detailing, handcrafted marionette realism. Inspired by fine woodworking and antique toy displays. Subtle fantasy undertones, no painterly texture, clean and digital clarity.

images.alt: A moody reinterpretation of Edward Hopper’s Nighthawks painting, set in a gritty Gotham-style city at night. Inside the warmly lit corner diner, now renamed “Koffee Korner” in vintage neon script, sit Batman, Robin, and Nightwing—each brooding or lost in thought. Batman sits silently in the shadows at the end of the counter, cape draped behind him, his eyes scanning the empty streets through the diner window. Nightwing leans on the counter, sipping coffee with a wry smirk, while Robin taps his gloved fingers on the counter, youthful energy barely contained.  The scene is filled with noir atmosphere—cool blues, deep shadows, and stark lighting cast from the diner’s glowing interior. Rain slicks the empty sidewalk outside, reflecting the neon glow. The city beyond is dark and deserted, hinting at danger just out of frame.  Art style blends Hopper’s realism with subtle comic book flair: detailed, dramatic lighting, cinematic depth, and slight stylization in the character design. 85mm lens effect, ultra-detailed, painterly texture.
